i blame valentines day
hunderds and hundreds of cards all decream "you're the ONE"
just imagine the hundeds and hundreds of wrenching late night phone calls, all over this idea and it's not just with love, it seems we're always looking for the one thing to make our lives complete...that job, that chance, that piece of cheesecake you were so badly craving that night and couldn't afford because you needed money for gas

when will waiting for the one be done..

i started to think about beleif, maybe it's not even adviseable to be an optimist, maybe pessimism is something we have to start applying daily like moisturizer, otherwise, how do you bounce back when reality batters your belief system and love does not as promised conquer all, is hope a drug we need to go off of or is it keeping us alive..

i'm wodering how long you need to do your affirmations, i want to beleive but nothing is happening, i just dont think it's working, i don't think it will work for me, you have to beleive love to receive love...i did find love, i beleived that there was someone out there for me and i met him, we had the best relationship, and then everything just fell apart, and i'm worried, i'm afraid that he took away my ability to beleive and i hate him for that because i always beleived before and now i just feel..lost,and i am trying to put myself out there but i feel hopeless

time...is every second of our lives controlled by FATE or is life just a series of random occurences if i was perpetually 10 minutes late, would my life be different....i can't help but wonder..

is timing everything?

So I get to school and there's about 4 cars in the parking lot.  It was the junior trip and I wasn't able to go because of my flight to NY today that's in a few hours.  So there's 8 juniors, me being one of them...all in one room for the whole day doing nothing.  I was the only girl and I was extremely anxious to leave.  

So lunch time...I went to the office to leave early, nobody there so I was gone.  I get home and crazy lady calls my house saying I disappeared and that I was missing blah blah.  At first, I was skeptical to leave without letting the office know...I just took my chances.

Whatever...now I'm just excited for today and tomorrow...party after party after the after party.  Also, got my Britney ticket to go see her in July and it's really good seats so yea rock on Britney and a big fuck you very much to school.

I approached her and we took a picture but it was very cool because she was so nice and on the show she's depicted as a total bitch but I didn't really care because she was one of my favorites on the show.

spring break.  i leave monday.  please let these days be relaxing.

i came to a concrete conclusion.  miami dislikes me oh so much.

i cant wait to be with my friends, my family, my old lifestyle that i am dying to go back to even if its only a week.

these past few weeks have been nothing but lonely and overslept.

all i need is a sign.  its like the more time that goes by, the emptier i become and one day, there will be nothing left but the sound of music.

i have nobody.  nothing.  i need my life back, i need to not be so weak.  i need not to cry.

i need change.


give me something. anything.

-marie.

I never thought I would say this, but

Britney's concert...awesome.

Some things that she did were very unexpected and the girl is just an amazing performer and her body is insane.  We thought we would see all the little girls shouting out her name but not at all.

I'll miss you Madeleine!

Bad day...not my best.

So I get home and the UPS guy gives me a huge box from Fortunoff's, I'm sitting there looking at it for about...ehh 40 minutes trying to figure out who it's from.

I open the box...hundreds and hundreds of styrofoam balls inside.  Funniest thing ever, I couldn't find the actual box with whatever was inside and I did after searching in there.  I open this box and it was the size of a set of plates or something.  I open that box and it filled with the balls again, so me and my mom are laughing so hard we didn't see the point.  Inside we found a gift from Michael's mom thanking me for letting him stay and taking care of him.  I got emotional haha.  That just made my whole day.

See you in Spring Break.

Theres nothing terribly wrong with feeling lost, so long as that feeling precedes some plan on your part to actually do something about it. Too often a person grows complacent with their disillusionment, perpetually wearing their "discomfort" like a favorite shirt. 

There is absolutely no point in sitting around and feeling sorry for youself. The great power you have is to let go ... focus on what you have, no that which has been mean or unkindly removed.


When you are low with nowhere to go remember this, when you open your eyes, your heart, your spirit, yourself, there you will find the stranger called hope.  I found this on my sign:

Aquarius..
Such is hope, heaven's own gift to struggling mortals, pervading, like some subtle essence from the skies, all things both good and bad.

I had deep thoughts today throughout the day, writing them down in class whenever they'd hit me so I would not forget =D
